        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverioDAI2"/>, p. 113, n. <citedRange>94</citedRange>, fig. 50</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.206</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>025000</citedRange></bibl>.
                Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#dthorn-thorn2009"/>, p. <citedRange>141</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63681"><name nymRef="#Ἐπιγένης">Ἐ<space quantity="1" unit="character"/>πιγένη<supplied reason="undefined" evidence="previouseditor">ς</supplied></name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63787"><name nymRef="#Εὐβάτας" type="patronymic">Εὐβάτα</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Epigenes fils d'Eubatas.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
                <p>Epigenes son of Eubatas.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Epigenes figlio di Eubatas.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The same man might be the honorand of <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr065700</ref>.</p>
                <p>The Torns' suggestion that the stele might come from the North Necropolis is based upon the idea that Italian excavations before World War II took place only 
                    in that Necropolis.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
